CTV News: “Explainable AI: The push to make sure machines don’t learn to be racist” (Singh quoted)
July 5, 2017 “Computers are going to become increasingly important parts of our lives, if they aren’t already, and the automation is just going to improve over time, so it’s increasingly important to know why these complicated systems are making the decisions that they are,” assistant professor of computer science at the University of California Irvine, Sameer Singh, told CTV’s Your Morning on Tuesday.
Read the full story at CTV News.
